  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/science/domains/linguistics/texts/describing-the-american-translation-of-post-to-anti/> ;
  schema:name "The American Translation of 'Post-' to 'Anti-': How a Temporal Prefix Became an Oppositional One" ;
  schema:description "In American intellectual discourse, the prefix 'post-' consistently translates from temporal ('after') to oppositional ('against'). Three structural causes: Puritan covenant binary, compressed epistemic field, and Cold War sorting. Documented across five cases with a self-reinforcing feedback loop." ;
